{{Underlinked|date=August 2016}}
'''Sebastian Martin''' (also known as ''Healer Baba'' by media)<ref name=q>{{cite web|author=Sushant Talwar Yesterday , 4:32 pm |url=http://www.thequint.com/india/2016/08/17/healer-baba-pastor-sebastian-martin-passes-away-in-mumbai |title=‘Healer Baba’ Pastor Sebastian Martin Passes Away in Mumbai |publisher=The Quint |date= |accessdate=2016-08-18}}</ref> was a controversial [[faith healer]] who claimed to cure all ailments through Jesus, including HIV, cancer, kidney, heart and other diseases through miracles.
He founded the Ashirward Prayer Centre as a venue for faith healing. Murdered rationalist [[Narendra Dabholkar]] had filed a police complaint against Sebastian and his associates for practicing [[alleged black magic]].<ref name=h>{{cite web|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/mumbai-news/controversial-miracle-man-passes-away-in-vasai/story-7ffxk1zATKeY2xQaZSOKQM.html |title=Controversial ‘miracle man’ passes away in Vasai &#124; mumbai news |publisher=Hindustan Times |date= |accessdate=2016-08-18}}</ref> and police had closed down the prayer center for its alleged black magic activities.
Sebastian shot to fame after his videos of ‘healing patients’ went viral on YouTube and other social media platforms.<ref name=q /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.india.com/news/cities/healer-baba-dr-sebastian-martin-found-dead-at-his-vasai-residence-1413654/ |title=Healer Baba Dr Sebastian Martin found dead at his Vasai residence |publisher=India.com |date= |accessdate=2016-08-18}}</ref>
Sebastian, a severe diabetic patient, died on 17 August 2016 at Bhuigaon after a prolonged illness. Some critics wrote articles about him stating that if he could heal others, why couldn't he heal himself.
